Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in your `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android **OnPause** = lost focus (maps to `Deactivated`); **OnStop** = fully backgrounded (maps to `Stopped`). iOS **DidEnterBackground** maps to `Stopped`.
- Keep handlers **fast** (<5s on Android, limited time on iOS) to avoid ANR/watchdog kills.
- On Android, the **back button can skip OnStop** and go straight to `OnDestroy` — save critical state in both.

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback parameters, override `Window.OnStopped()` instead — it fires on all platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
// In App.cs
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* runs on all platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```
